value.0: A young man with robes and a staff - probably a mage. He seems a bit jumpy.
Though Kohlingen is a city renowned on Amia for its holiness and the righteousness of its causes, it also fields the best heavy foot on the islands outside of Barak Runedar.

These cloaks are made of fine dark blue and golden cloth. An emblem of a singular golden dragon sits in the center of this finely crafted garment, the symbol of the Defenders of Kohlingen, the defenders of justice and those who would ask for their aid, sworn to uphold these values and loyal servants of Kohlingen's Justicar, these warriors have been selectivly fit to wear each of the hand-crafted capes that you now hold in your hands. A fine item indeed to any lucky to ever get their hands on one, though if a member of the Defenders where to see a none-Defender wearing it... well they could become slightly upset!

OOC NOTE: Only wearable by a Defender of Kohlingen.

Value.value: *The man starts in alarm when you approach.* Oh, you're not one of those beasts. Sorry. These things are most unusual.
Did Mister Snow send you? We're pretty sure these nasty beasts are responsible for his missing livestock. They're aberrations, though... These tunnels are not for the faint of heart.
If you'd like to help, go on in. But be wary... Aberrations are known for bringing madness upon those who try to interact with them. Even in battle, they may leave your mind addled or broken.

I have some gold and jewelry I can spare to thank you for aiding in stopping these creatures, so any help you can offer would be much appreciated. Just bring me something to examine and I may be able able to put an end to this.
This... is certainly something. I'll look it over and see if I can figure out how to be rid of these foul beasts. Thank you. Here's the reward. You've certainly earned it.
Hello again. Thanks for the help. If you're still feeling up to it, there's a Southport guard over on the west coast who's looking for help. Can reach him by going through the west gate in Southport.
You just need to head into the tunnels here. Look for something especially unusual that I can examine to try to get these things out of here.

value.0: The plant upon which the ever-popular sweetberry grows. Fairly small-sized, these plants have been known to grow larger when cultivated as house plants; this practice is rather uncommon, however, perhaps because of the fey that are usually attracted to houses in which the plants are potted....

The Sweetberry is a highly prized item for Cordorian children, to others, completely useless.  Commonly stuck on the end of a stick and licked, the sweetberry has a powerfully sweet taste that most adults find overwhelming.  Except in Amia, where they are enjoyed by almost all, sometimes even a little too much, in the case of an ex-assassin who craves them with a passion.
This is just a grass. Nothing to explore.

A faint, continual sound of gibbering voices can be heard from the tunnels below, little more than scratched out holes in the dirt.
